          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-09 20:16:35" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the act of clearing someone of transgression</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to acquit</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to set free</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to remove guilt</Gloss>
                <Gloss>acquittal</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages the process of acquittal takes the form of a direct statement, for example, ‘to say, You are not guilty’ or ‘…, You no longer have sin’ or, as expressed idiomatically in some instances, ‘…, Sin is no longer on your head’ or ‘…, Your sins are now given back to you.’</Comments>
